name: USS Hood
note:
NCC-42296
<cgmzdesc:This is a Starfleet vessel with registry number NCC-42296.
Under the command of Captain DeSoto, it survived the Battle of Wolf 359 and saw service until the late 24th century.
It was retired to the Wolf 359 Memorial Station.
>

name: USS Columbia
note:
NCC-71102
<cgmzdesc:This is a Starfleet vessel with registry number NCC-71102.
Originally under the command of Admiral J.P. Hanson, it was wrecked during the Battle of Wolf 359.
It was later repaired and became a museum piece at the Wolf 359 Memorial Station. 
>
profile: The USS Columbia, a salvaged Galaxy-Class starship.

name: USS Ibn Sina
note:
NCC-70532
<cgmzdesc:This is a Starfleet vessel with registry number NCC-70532.
Originally under the command of Captain Alan Hutton, it was disabled during the Battle of Wolf 359. Thanks to it's rugged construction, most of the spaceframe and crew survived
It is now a museum piece at the Wolf 359 Memorial Station. 
>
profile: The USS Ibn Sina, a salvaged Parliament-Class starship.

name: USS Kaneda
note:
NX-62498
<cgmzdesc:This is a prototype Starfleet vessel with registry number NX-62498.
The Kaneda was the second of three Akira-Class protytpes. The call to action came while the Akira was being refit and the Tetsuo was still under construction. As such, the Kaneda was the only Akira sent with the fleet to Wolf 359, where it proved extremely effective against the Borg.
It was recovered and is now a tourable museum piece at the Wolf 359 Memorial Station. 
>
profile: The USS Kaneda, a salvaged prototype Akira-Class starship.

name: USS Mjoliner

NCC-3117

It was recovered and is now a tourable museum piece at the Wolf 359 Memorial Station.
